Model Interface:

The model interface consists of a navigation pane, tools and actions, and a variable filter panel.

Elements of the Model Interface:

1. Headline: Name of this model, goal, and model type.
2. Model Tools:
  Version—Displays selected version and opens the Version History Action menu
  Change Outcome—Change the selected outcome
  Deploy Model—Deploy the model
  Publish to Quip—Publish this model to Quip
  Properties—Rename or move model
  Delete—Delete this model

3. Navigation Pane: Move between Model Performance, Settings, and Predictions.
  Headline:
    AREA	NAME	DESCRIPTION
    1	Model Name	Name of this model
    2	Model Goal	Desired outcome
    3	Model Type	
      Regression
      Binary Classification
      Multiclass Classification
